title: MCC Shift Change: Swing Shift, Sunday, 20-Feb-2022
text: LCLS HXR: Beam to CXI/XPP until 21:00, switch to XCS. LCLS SXR: 10 Hz beam to TMO until 21:00. FACET: Work on transmission, attempt wire scans + possibly matching in LI19 & downstream.

title: Asked PEM to take a look at 11-2, we're seeing the same structure on the energy BPMs as yesterday
* Re: Sent QE Measurement and Dark Current plots to FACET physics log
text: This QE number is about twenty times too low... with the Faraday Cup inserted the QE calculated on the laser panel reads about 1.2E-4, which is consistent with the numbers (cross-referencing LCLS).

title: 11-2 MOD faulted - related to PEM work?
* PEM is working on it, says it will be back in a few minutes. Re: 11-2 MOD faulted - related to PEM work?
11-2 back on, beam is back.
text: Cordell ranged the thyratron slightly, but couldn't find anything else wrong with the modulator.

title: * Fixed. Re: 13-5 has low amplitude. CATERed 155283.
FLEM wants to make big changes in L2 and L3.
text: Not sure why this made transmission worse last time... but we are on energy and the orbit is quite flat (although maybe we get better transmission with non-flat orbits going into the W chicane), so I suspect that matching is a problem.

title: Lost beam again
SSRL-BLDO dayshift report 2022-Feb-20
text: Program beam to users w/500ma 5min. freq. fill mode. 1745 spear lost beam due to power issue. Beam lines: All open except BL17 which was closed after a MM1 priority 1 Logic fault. Faults/Alarms: @1210 BL17 MM1 priority 1 Logic fault. Reset fault contacted MPS/PPS personnel and BL17 was taken off line till staff can access next week. Experiments: User on 2-1 had software issues @0600 this morning. Support staff was contacted and they are up and running. Other: LN delivery this morning at shift change.

title: Looks like 476MHz master oscillator is dead -- will try replacing fuse
3/4A slo blo fuse is blown
text: The box of fuses that I left in this area a year or two ago is no longer there, so I'll have to go find an MDL 3/4. Also, the plastic fuse holder was damaged the last time someone replaced the fuse. I was able to get it out, but will have to file a new slot in the plastic in order to use it again.

title: Got a few mA stored, then RF tripped off
Efficiency was horrible, will need to adjust Hettel knob
text: Losing the timing system means SPEAR-to-booster phase will be some random value now. Will try to work fast to get the Hettel knob in the ballpark, then fine tune during injection.

title: First walkthrough complete, scroll pump outside XCS clanking, sent mail to Matt Hayes.
Filling at 54mA/minute, beamlines open except 17
BEAMS - 500mA, autofill to RUN mode
TUNE mode to ootch up the Q meter
text: Down to 250mV, will see if I can get it back up to 300-350.

title: 16-6 has tripped several times this shift, errors panel shows a lot of water faults, CATERing
21-4 MOD faulted & halved the HXR intensity while simultaneously doubling the SXR
text: Initially quite confusing ...

title: Transmission up to 90%! Ben found some quads that needed to be moved.
CXI/XPP/TMO done with beam. Starting E change.
text: CXI and XCS traded off ~5 minutes to finish observations

title: CXI/XPP/TMO done with beam. Starting E change.
text: CXI and XCS traded off ~5 minutes to finish observations

title: * Re: Transmission up to 90%! Ben found some quads that needed to be moved.
text: The EPICS quads in LI19 got moved quite a bit over the last few days (maybe by FLEM?). Moving them back towards their previous values + tweaking energy + steering got us good transmission again, saved a config & reference orbit.

title: Shift summary: Sunday swing
text: SUMMARY: User beam for 10.9 hours of this 12-hour shift. Lost beam once due to beamline priority 1 fault, and once due to a master oscillator blown fuse. The average fill rate is about 50mA/minute, and the average calculated efficiency is about 95%. INJECTOR: Up to 350mV Q. Tuned once between fills. SPEAR: Lost beam at 12:10pm with an indicated priority 1 fault at BL17 on one PLC, âBL3-0â fault indicated on another PLC, and priority 2 indicated in the duty operatorâs area. In any case, the faults all reset and SPEAR was refilled to 500mA 30 minutes after the dump. Lost beam at 5:47pm with a clear indication of timing system fault. Replaced a blown fuse in the SPEAR master oscillator. SPEAR was refilled to 500mA 35 minutes after the fault.

title: Incoming Duty Tech: Christina Eshelman (1400-2430)
Plan for going to 17 keV
text: We are going to try to scale up the current config while keeping BC2 at 4.50 GeV by adding all the L3 stations we have available. First we'll scale it up to 12 GeV and see how it performs there before going up to 14.067 GeV. We will then try to tune up the FEL from there. If this doesn't work, we can try loading a config from 2/16 (the last time we ran at 14.067 GeV/ 17 keV). However, this config has BC2 at 4.75 GeV and we might not be able to get there without 24-5. We do have more L3 stations available now than we did last week, which is why we're going to try adding all of them first. MEC will call us when they're ready to start the change.
